" Disable arrow keys
map <up> <nop>
map <down> <nop>
map <left> <nop>
map <right> <nop>
imap <up> <nop>
imap <down> <nop>
imap <left> <nop>
imap <right> <nop>

" Remapping C-s requires flow control to be disabled in .bash/.zshrc
map <C-s> <esc>:w<CR>
imap <C-s> <esc>:w<CR>
map <C-t> <esc>:tabnew<CR>
map <C-x> <C-w>c
map <C-n> :cn<CR>
map <C-p> :cp<CR>

" Disable Ex mode
map Q <Nop>
" Disable K looking stuff up
map K <Nop>

" Let's be reasonable, shall we?
nmap k gk
nmap j gj

inoremap <Tab> <C-P>


